MONGO_URI=
ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET=
PORT=5001

GOOGLE_DRIVE_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id
GOOGLE_DRIVE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret
GOOGLE_DRIVE_REDIRECT_URI=https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground
GOOGLE_DRIVE_REFRESH_TOKEN=your_refresh_token
GOOGLE_DRIVE_FOLDER_ID=optional_folder_id


# Go to Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# Create/select a project.
# Go to APIs & Services > Library.
# Search Google Drive API and enable it.
# Go to APIs & Services > OAuth consent screen.
# Choose External unless you have Workspace.
# Fill app name/email.
# Add yourself as a Test user.
# Go to APIs & Services > Credentials.
# Click Create credentials > OAuth client ID.
# Choose Web application.
# Add this under Authorized redirect URIs:
# https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground
# Copy:Client ID → GOOGLE_DRIVE_CLIENT_ID
# Client secret → GOOGLE_DRIVE_CLIENT_SECRET

# Get refresh token
# Open OAuth Playground: https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground/
# Click the gear icon top-right.
# Check Use your own OAuth credentials.
# Paste your Client ID and Client Secret.
# In scopes, enter:
# https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive.file
# Click Authorize APIs.
# Sign in with the Google account whose 15 GB Drive you want to use.
# Click Exchange authorization code for tokens.
# Copy Refresh token → GOOGLE_DRIVE_REFRESH_TOKEN.

Your .env should look like:
GOOGLE_DRIVE_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id
GOOGLE_DRIVE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret
GOOGLE_DRIVE_REDIRECT_URI=https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground
GOOGLE_DRIVE_REFRESH_TOKEN=your_refresh_token
GOOGLE_DRIVE_FOLDER_ID=optional_folder_id
Small warning: if your OAuth app stays in Testing, Google refresh tokens can expire. For stable use, publish the OAuth app or be ready to generate a new refresh token later.
Official refs: Google credentials guide https://developers.google.com/workspace/guides/create-credentials and OAuth Playground https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground/